title: grandma's salad
directions: Put dry Jell-O in bottom of bowl.
Add fruit cocktail; stir. Add mini marshmallows, any amount you want.
Add cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Mix and let stand to set.
Mix before serving.

title: chinese noodles cookies(very good)
directions: Melt together morsels and peanut butter over hot water (not boiling) or in a microwave for 1 minute and stir.
If not long enough, give it another 30 seconds to 1 minute.
When melted, stir in Chinese noodles.
Mix well and drop on wax paper by teaspoon. Let harden.

title: jimmy cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugars.
Separate eggs; add yolks to mixture.
Mix flour and baking powder.
Add alternately with coffee.
Add nuts and jimmies.
Beat egg whites; fold into batter. Put into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Done when toothpick comes out clean.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Boil cider and spices for 15 minutes.
Add honey, juices and orange peel.
Simmer for 2 to 3 minutes.

title: brown bag apple pie
directions: Make pie shell using your own recipe.
Pare, core and quarter apples, then halve each quarter.
You should have about 7 cups of apples.
Place in a large bowl.

title: peanut butter yogurt pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate.
May be frozen.

title: nacho dip
directions: Spread bean dip on pizza pan.
Peel, pit and mash avocado and mix with lemon juice, salt, pepper, sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning mix.
Put on top of bean dip.
Sprinkle top with onions, tomatoes and olives.
Cover with shredded cheese.
May be served cold or heat in oven or microwave to melt cheese.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: shelley's salsa
directions: *May add additional jalapenos if desired or if a hot salsa is needed, add 1 Scotch bonnet pepper.

title: italian steak rolls
directions: Bone and remove the fat from the steak. Cut into 8 pieces. Beat pieces with a meat tenderizer until flat and as even as possible.

title: praline sweet potatoes
directions: Butter one 2-quart casserole dish. Preheat oven to 350° (175°C). In a mixing bowl, combine the sweet potatoes, sugar, vanilla extract, eggs and cream. Blend well and spread evenly in casserole dish.

title: fudge pudding
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Stir in 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Add 1/2 cup milk and 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Blend slightly and stir in 3 tablespoon of melted butter.
Put in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch greased pan.

title: banana fruit cake
directions: Beat shortening and gradually add sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs.
Beat until thick and lemon colored.
Combine dry ingredients and add alternately with bananas.
Blend in fruit, raisins and nuts.
Pour into a 9-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool and spread with glaze.

title: strawberries and cream
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine condensed milk and water.
Mix well.
Add pudding mix and beat until well blended.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon 2 cups pudding mixture into 4-quart serving bowl.
Top with half the cake cubes, half the strawberries and half the remaining pudding mixture.
Repeat layering, ending with pudding mixture.
Garnish with strawberries. Chill at least 4 hours.

title: ooh yuck!
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in seasoning packet from noodles, soy sauce and cooked broccoli.
Cook noodles, using package directions.
Add to ground beef mixture.
Mix well; cook until heated through.
Serve with additional soy sauce.

title: buckeye balls
directions: Cream peanut butter and oleo until creamy and gradually add sugar.
Roll in small balls.

title: sailor's salad
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions; drain. Combine macaroni, celery, onions, crabmeat and eggs.
Blend mayonnaise and French dressing.
Toss macaroni mixture with dressing; chill.
Serve on lettuce.
Yields 8 servings.

title: potato au gratin
directions: Place potatoes in lightly greased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with rosemary and pepper.
Combine with milk and gravy mix; pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until tender.
Yields 6 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add bananas and eggs; beat well.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt; add to batter. Pour into a greased loaf pan and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: zany winter drink
directions: Break up the cinnamon sticks and put them in a "tea ball" along with the cloves.
Put the water in a large pot (should be at least a six-quart size) and bring to boil, boiling for three minutes.
Turn off heat; put in the tea bags and "tea ball" containing the whole cloves and broken cinnamon sticks.
Let tea steep for 30 minutes.
Remove the tea ball and bags; pour in the sugar, stirring until dissolved.
Add pineapple juice and lemonade; stir.
Heat until brew is hot enough to drink.

title: summer salad
directions: Slice potatoes, eggs and lettuce.
Blend dressing and pour over vegetables.
Garnish with sliced tomatoes. Serves 4.

title: chicken and succotash skillet
directions: Lightly coat chicken pieces with 1 tablespoon of flour.
Melt half the butter in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cool 5 to 7 minutes, turning once, until lightly golden.
Remove to plate with slotted spoon.
Reduce heat to medium.
Melt remaining butter in skillet; add onion and cook about 4 minutes, stirring often.
Add bell pepper and cook 2 to 3 minutes, until onion is translucent and pepper is crisp-tender.

title: spinach dip in bread bowl
directions: Slice top off bread.
Scoop out inside of bread.
Cut bread which was scooped out into bite size pieces.
Set aside.
Squeeze out spinach.
Combine with all other ingredients to make dip. Spoon dip into bread.
Chill until ready to serve or if desired, wrap in aluminum foil and heat at 200° for 2 hours.
Serve with bite size bread pieces and fresh vegetables.

title: baked french toast with blueberry sauce
directions: Slice bread into 12 to 14 slices about 3/4-inch thick.
Place on a 10 1/2 x 15 1/2 x 1-inch cookie sheet.
Whisk egg, milk, baking powder and vanilla together and slowly pour it over the bread, turning to coat the bread completely.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours or overnight.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Boil sliced zucchini and onions in salted water until barely cooked.
Drain.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Add cheese, salt and pepper.
Beat egg and milk.
Pour over zucchini.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: potato patties
directions: To potatoes, add egg, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix well. Shape in 6 patties . Dip in flour, then brown slowly in butter, about 5 minutes on each side.
Makes 6 servings.

title: ora avant's cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water to dissolve.
Mix plain gelatin with cold water.
Add plain gelatin to hot gelatin; stir to dissolve.
Stir all ingredients into Jell-O mixture.
Chill in refrigerator until set or firm.
May also add chopped apple and nuts to this.

title: peanut chicken
directions: Mix peanut oil, soy sauce and sugar together in a large pan. After the sugar is dissolved, add chicken
parts.
Bring chicken in sauce to a boil, stirring occasionally.	Cover
and cook
for about 45 minutes or until wings are
tender.
Remove chicken from sauce and place on serving tray.
Chop
the stems of
green onions
and
mix together with 1/4	cup
chopped peanuts.
Pour sauce over chicken and sprinkle with
onion and peanut mixture.

title: chipped apple pie
directions: Prepare pie crust.
Place chipped apples into crust.
Combine sugar, cinnamon, salt and melted margarine.
Add beaten egg.
Pour over chipped apples.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve with ice cream.

title: venison stew
directions: Place preceding ingredients in your slow cooker in order given.
Stir until mixed, then cover and cook on low heat overnight or 10 to 12 hours.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Can be baked 1 hour or longer.

title: diabetic peachy pie
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over water in small mixing bowl.
Place in pan of hot water.
Heat until dissolved.
Add ginger ale; stir. Add peaches. Chill until it begins to thicken.
Spoon into pie crust and chill until firm.
May be served with low calorie whipped topping.
Equals 1 fruit, 1 bread and 2 fats.

title: hawaiian cabbage
directions: Dissolve the Jello and gelatin in 1 1/2 cups boiling water. Add 1 cup ice cubes.
Add lemon juice and chill until partially set.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour in 9x13 pan.
Chill until set.

title: chicken under yum
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Dip chicken in butter and arrange in pan.
Place a slice of cheese on top of each piece of chicken.
Sprinkle dry stuffing mix over chicken and cheese.
Mix soup and milk.
Pour over top of stuffing mix.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.
Serve with chips.

title: angel food lemonade cake
directions: Soften ice cream; add can of lemonade and stir until well mixed.
Slice cake in 2 or 3 layers.
Spread with ice cream in between layers.
Ice with remainder of ice cream mixture.
Serve immediately, topped with strawberries or return to freezer.
Let set out 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: tapioca pudding
directions: Add tapioca to milk.
Beat together the eggs, sugar and cornstarch; add to milk-tapioca mixture when about cooled.
Add some hot milk.
When cold, add whipped cream, bananas, nuts, pineapple or whatever you wish.

title: un aperitive de ensalada
directions: In food processor, chop green onions, cilantro and cheeses. In large bowl, layer the green onions, diced tomatoes, diced avocados, cheeses and salsa; sprinkle with Lawry's seasoned salt. Marinate in refrigerator overnight.
Toss before serving with chips.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a Bundt pan for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: 5-hour beef stew
directions: Place all ingredients in an ovenproof, covered bowl and cook at 250° for 4 1/2 to 5 hours.

title: shrimp scampi(microwave)
directions: Place margarine in 2-quart casserole. Microwave at High until melted, 1 to 2 1/2 minutes.
Stir in lemon juice, garlic and salt. Add shrimp; toss to coat.
Cover.
Microwave at High until shrimp is pink, opaque and tender, 4 1/2 to 7 minutes, stirring twice.

title: indian pudding
directions: Mix all together, adding the margarine last.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours, stirring three times while cooking.
Serve with favorite topping.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: In a pan combine soup and milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring often.
Remove from heat and add cheese, mayonnaise and salt. Stir until cheese melts.
Blend in sherry.
Add shrimp, noodles, onions and mushrooms.
Mix well and turn into casserole dish. Bake, covered, 25 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and add a bit of shredded cheese on top.
Bake 10 minutes more.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat all but corn with eggbeater.
Stir in corn.
Pour into well-buttered casserole.
Set in a pan of water.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: lamb stew - vintage recipe
directions: Cook lamb for 1 3/4 hours.
Let the lamb cool until the fat rises to the top.
Then scrape the fat off and take the meat off of the bone.
Add onions, carrots, celery, salt and pepper to the lamb and cook for 1 hour.
Add the potatoes and cook the stew for another 3/4 to 1 hour, until the potatoes cook down and thicken the stew.
Serves 8.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together, except last 2 ingredients.
Mold into a loaf pan.
Cook for 1 hour.
Mix together mushroom soup and tomato sauce.
Heat.
Pour over meat loaf and cook for 30 minutes.

title: chop suey
directions: Brown pork chops; then add cabbage and peppers.
Steam 10 minutes.
Then add rest of ingredients.
Add salt to taste. Cover and cook on low heat for 3/4 hour.

title: yankee doodle salad
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese according to directions on the box, adding the butter, milk and cheese.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill before serving.

title: curried fruit
directions: Mix margarine, curry powder and brown sugar and pour over fruit.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Goes well with ham or chicken.

title: pfeffernuesse
directions: Mix the butter and molasses in a saucepan and melt over low heat.
Cool to room temperature.
Stir together all dry ingredients in a large bowl; set aside.
Stir the egg into the molasses mixture and gradually stir in the flour mixture.
Cover and chill one hour or until dough is easy to handle.
Divide dough into 12 portions. On a lightly floured surface roll each piece into a 10-inch rope. Cut the ropes into 1/2-inch pieces.
Place the pieces 1/2-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350 for 10 to 12 minutes or until edges are firm and bottoms are lightly browned.
Cool on paper towels.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Brown hamburger and set aside.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, 1/2 cup butter (melted), onion, soup, sour cream and cheese; stir well.
Spoon into a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour remaining butter over top.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, egg, onion and salt.
Prepare meatballs and set aside.
Mix in large saucepan chili sauce, lemon juice and grape jelly.
Add meatballs.
Simmer 1 to 2 hours.
(To reduce the fat in the sauce, you may cook the meatballs first in the microwave and drain; then add to sauce and simmer until heated through.)

title: baked turkey-stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cut a slice off top of each tomato and scoop out pulp; reserve for other use.
Sprinkle inside of tomatoes with salt and turn upside-down to drain.
In small saucepan, melt butter and blend in flour.
Cook, stirring until bubbly.
Off heat, stir in milk.
Put back over low heat and cook, stirring until smooth and thickened. Stir in turkey, celery, onions, nuts and 1/4 cup cheese.
Season to taste with seasoned salt and pepper.
Fill tomato shells with the mixture.
Arrange in shallow baking dish or pie plate. Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup cheese.
Bake at 375°
for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: carrot salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; chill until thickened. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into lightly greased mold or individual molds.
Chill until firm.
Serves 6.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Season raw shrimp with salt, pepper and cayenne pepper (to taste) and set aside.
Melt margarine.
Add onions, celery, bell pepper and garlic.
Cook slowly in uncovered heavy pot until onions wilt.
Add shrimp and let simmer, stirring occasionally, 30 minutes.
Dissolve cornstarch in water.
Add to mixture.
Cook 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: blackberry pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and add lemon juice and mix. Place in unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 450° after putting butter on top.
Cover with strips and then bake.
Check after 20 minutes.
Temperature adjustment may be necessary.
Bake until done.

title: chicken fried steak
directions: Using a meat mallet or rolling pin, pound each beef cutlet to 1/4-inch thickness. Sprinkle garlic salt on both sides of each cutlet. Pour flour onto a pie plate or shallow bowl and coat each cutlet. Refrigerate until most of the flour has been absorbed (10 to 20 minutes). Pour buttermilk into a shallow bowl or pie plate. Dip each cutlet into buttermilk, then dredge each in another coating of flour, shaking off excess. (Reserve remaining gravy for making gravy.) Heat 2 tablespoons of the oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Add 2 of the steaks and cook until golden brown on both sides, about 4 to 5 minutes per side. Transfer to a serving platter. Repeat with remaining 2 steaks, adding remaining oil as needed. Stir remaining flour into skillet. Stir in broth, milk, salt and pepper with a wire whisk. Cook, stirring constantly over high heat until thickened. Pour over steaks and serve. Makes 4 servings.

title: mocha float
directions: Into 8 ounce glass, measure first 3 ingredients.
Gradually add enough club soda to fill glass 3/4 full; stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add chocolate ice cream; stir.
Serve with spoon and straw.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray muffin pans with nonstick spray. Mix first five ingredients together.
Use enough mustard to stick ingredients together.

title: our traditional cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill overnight.

title: chocolate covered peanuts
directions: Melt almond bark and chips; stir in peanuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Cool.

title: swiss pecan pleasers
directions: Press rolls into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Pour on top of crescent roll dough.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let set 5 minutes.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares and serve hot!

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Layer meat, soup, cheese, chops and Ro-Tel in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer until pan is full.
Top with cheese.
Cook at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: crackerjack cookies
directions: Cream sugars and butter. Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well. Sift together flour, baking powder and soda.
Combine flour and egg mixture.
Add oatmeal, coconut and cereal.
Mix well.
(If too sticky, may need to add a little more flour.)
Drop by heaping spoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto greased baking sheet.
Bake in oven preheated to 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove at once.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: pea salad
directions: Thaw peas and drain well.
Add rest of ingredients and season to taste with salt and pepper.
Toss lightly and refrigerate.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Mix sugar, oleo, syrup and salt.
Bring to boil.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from stove.
Add soda; stir well.
Spray Pam on inside of large brown sack.
Put popped corn into sack.
Pour syrup over the popcorn.
Stir well.
Cook in microwave on Full power for 1 1/2 minutes.
Take out.
Shake well.
Cook 1 1/2 minutes more.
Shake well.
Cook for 30 seconds.
Shake.
Open bag.
Let cool.

title: chocolate yum-yum
directions: Mix Oreos and 1/3 cup of melted butter and press in 9 x 12-inch pan and freeze.
Mix softened ice cream with instant coffee; spread over Oreo mixture and freeze.
In saucepan, mix chocolate squares or cocoa, 1/3 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons margarine and Pet milk.
Cook until thickened.
Cool and put on top of ice cream mixture.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook water, sugar, cornstarch, jello and Karo syrup until thickened, then cool.
Slice or quarter strawberries into a 9-inch baked pie shell.
Pour cooled, thickened mixture over strawberries.
Refrigerate.
Top with Cool Whip when serving. Yield:
6 servings.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Make cake as directed on package and use a 13 x 9-inch pan. After cake cools, poke all over top of cake and pour Kahlua over it.
Let stand overnight.

title: super burgers
directions: Combine 1/4 cup soup with remaining ingredients except oil. Shape into patties.
Heat oil in large skillet and brown burgers on both sides.
(Drain excess fat.)
Combine remaining soup with 1/2 cup water.
Pour over burgers and cook over low heat about 20 minutes, turning occasionally and stirring sauce as needed.
Add water as needed to sauce if it becomes too thick.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Cook to a rolling boil. Do not stir.
Pour over warm cake.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan. Add syrup and sugar. Bring to a boil and boil 3 minutes on stove top. Add soda and salt and stir. Pour over popcorn in brown grocery sack and shake or stir in large bowl. Microwave 1
1/2 minutes. Stir or shake. Microwave for another 1 1/2 minutes. Spread on cookie sheet to cool.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Put bacon, potatoes and onion in baking dish.
Add butter, milk, salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are tender.

title: apple dip
directions: With mixer blend cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add pecans. Wash and slice Granny Smith apples to serve with dip.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill for an hour.
Take out of refrigerator; roll in nuts.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: microwave meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Form meatballs.
Place 8 to 10 on paper towel-lined plate.
Cover with paper towel and microwave 3 minutes on High.

title: barbie's breakfast drink
directions: Blend juice and sugar in blender for a frothy delight!

title: cinnamon nut squares
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cream margarine, sugars and egg yolk until light and fluffy.
Combine flour, cinnamon and salt.
Add to beaten mixture and continue beating until blended.
Spread into ungreased jelly roll pan.
Beat egg white until just foamy.
Spread evenly on top of dough.
Sprinkle with nuts and press in lightly. Bake 40 minutes.
Cut into squares while still hot.

title: diet cabbage soup
directions: Add water to cook.
Cook until all vegetables are tender.
Add beef broth, if desired.

title: chili dip
directions: Combine all ingredients
in
top of double boiler.
Cook over low heat,
stirring frequently, until cheese melts.
Serve warm with taco chips.
Yield:
About 1 1/2 quarts dip.

title: taco pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Meanwhile, place pizza crust on pizza pan or baking sheet.
Mix tomato sauce and taco seasoning.
Spread over crust.
Dot with beef; sprinkle with chili peppers and cheese.
Bake in 425 °oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until meat is cooked and cheese is melted.
Sprinkle with lettuce, tomato and corn chips.
Serves 4.

title: grandma's fruit salad
directions: Make Jell-O as directed, less 1 cup cold water.
Add remaining ingredients, stir and chill overnight.
Stir well before serving.

title: maple nut squares
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.
Slowly add oil.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing until blended.
Spread batter in greased 7 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: zucchini parmesan
directions: Saute onion until soft.
Add zucchini, salt and pepper.
Cook 5 minutes.
Toss with cheese before serving.

title: coconut pancakes
directions: Combine egg, sour cream and buttermilk.
Sift together the flour, soda, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add dry ingredients to liquids.
Mix until batter is lumpy; add coconut and extract but don't overbeat.
Spoon batter onto hot griddle.
When done, place on plate and sprinkle with flaked coconut.
Serve with cream of coconut (takes the place of syrup).
Makes 8 to 10 pancakes.

title: chris' lo mein
directions: Boil 5 quarts water. Drop noodles in boiling water for 2 minutes. Drain and rinse thoroughly.
Fry onions in 4 tablespoons oil until brown.
Add all other ingredients.
Stir in gravy and mix.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Press a crisscross on each cookie with a fork dipped in water.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes until golden.
Cool on cookie sheet about 1 minute before removing.

title: leila's feather rolls
directions: Combine yeast, 2 teaspoons
sugar and warm water.
Stir until dissolved.
Scald milk and add shortening, 1/3 cup sugar and salt. Stir until
shortening
is
melted.
Beat
eggs and stir into milk mixture.
Stir in yeast and 3 cups flour.
Beat well with a mixer.
Stir
in
remaining
1/2 cups flour, it will
be a sticky
dough.
Cover
and
refrigerate
overnight. Turn out on a floured
board
and shape into crescent, cloverleaf or Parker House rolls.
Let stand 4 hours, covered with a cloth.
Brush with melted butter
and
bake
at
for
10 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 36 to 48 rolls.

title: green bean-onion bake
directions: Alternate layers of green beans and onion rings in a 2-quart casserole, ending with onion rings on top.
Blend together soup and milk.
Pour over vegetables.
Blend slightly. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 portions.

title: jarrett house pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: chipped beef spread or dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except pecans and butter; mix well and put into heatproof serving dish.
Saute pecans in the butter and sprinkle over top of cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 15 to 20 minutes or until warm, but not runny.
Serve with corn chips.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Combine all ingredients, except tortilla chips.
Let simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve with crumbled tortilla chips in bowls.

title: cheesy green beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain bacon, reserving 1/4 cup drippings.
Crumble bacon.
Reserve 2 tablespoons.
Microwave beans as directed on package; drain well.
Add mushrooms and onion to reserved 1/4 cup drippings in skillet.
Cook and stir on medium heat 10 minutes.
Drain.
Add bacon, hot cooked green beans and pepper; mix lightly.
Spoon into 2-quart serving dish.
Microwave Cheez Whiz as directed on label.
Pour over green bean mixture. Sprinkle with reserved crumbled bacon.
Makes 10 servings.

title: orange-flavored pecans
directions: Cook milk and sugar slowly, to a soft ball stage.
Add orange rind.
Cook for a few minutes more.
Add margarine and pecans. Stir to coat all pecans.
Turn out on waxed paper and separate.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a loaf pan lightly with some shortening.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten eggs, mashed bananas and lemon juice until well blended.
Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add to shortening/banana mixture.
Mix until well blended.
Add nuts and lemon zest if desired.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes. Remove from pan.

title: banana bread
directions: Following is both basic dough and feeding.

title: cranberry salad ring
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Chill until consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Combine next 6 ingredients and mix well.
Fold fruit mixture into gelatin mixture.
Pour into slightly oiled 10-cup ring mold.
Chill until set.
Unmold on lettuce leaves.
Fill center of ring with mayonnaise and garnish with orange slices, if desired.
Makes 20 servings.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown beef, add onions and cook until tender.
Add tomatoes mixed with chili powder, cumin, garlic and kidney beans.
Simmer for 1/2 hour (at least).
Add cracker crumbs just before serving.

title: grandma jane's easy chicken dinner
directions: Remove fat from chicken and cube.
Place cubed chicken in bottom of crock-pot.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook on high for at least 2 hours or until chicken is done, stirring occasionally.

title: poppy seed coffee cake
directions: Let the poppy seed soak in the buttermilk in refrigerator overnight.
Cream the shortening with the sugar well.
Add the eggs one at a time and beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour, baking powder, soda and salt together.
Add alternately with the buttermilk mixture.
Blend in vanilla.
Grease Bundt mold well or angel food cake pan.
Pour into mold.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°. Cool in mold before removing.
Plain powdered sugar or a glaze may be drizzled over the cake when cooled.

title: georgia pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs one at a time. Add flour and baking powder gradually.
Add vanilla.
Add milk last.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Cook for 1 hour at 325°.
Turn oven off and leave cake in for 10 minutes.
Let cake sit in Bundt pan 20 minutes before removing.

title: butterfinger cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spoon into little balls and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Place all ingredients in pan and heat.
Serve with oyster crackers, plain or seasoned.
See recipe for Party Crackers.

title: baked barbecue chicken
directions: Season chicken with garlic salt and seasoned pepper in large baking pan.
Mix syrup with barbecue sauce.
Pour over chicken and bake at 400° in covered pan for 35 minutes and then uncover and bake for another 35 minutes, basting until well glazed.

title: chocolate layered dessert
directions: Pour milk into large bowl.
Add pudding mix; beat with wire whisk 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Gently stir in 2 cups Cool Whip.
Arrange 1/2 of the cake cubes into 3 1/2-quart serving bowl. Drizzle with 1/2 of the chocolate syrup.
Layer with 1/2 of the chopped candy bars and 1/2 of the pudding mix.
Repeat layers ending with pudding mix.
Refrigerate 1 hour or until ready to serve.
Garnish with remaining Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with additional chopped candy bars.
Makes about 12 servings.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Combine shortening, sugar, vanilla, egg and milk; beat until fluffy.
In another bowl, mix separately, combining the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add with creamy mixture.
Roll and separate into half.
Chill for 1 hour.
Roll out on floured surface and cut into shapes.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Add sugar crystals if desired.

title: grits and cheese
directions: Heat the water to a boil.
Remove from heat and add the remaining ingredients.
Stir until all blended.
Put back on fire and bring to a boil.
Place in greased 13 x 9-inch dish and bake, uncovered, at 300° for 1 hour or until set.

title: cranberry pie
directions: Grease 10-inch pie plate.
Spread cranberries on bottom. Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar and nuts over cranberries.
Mix the rest of the ingredients together; pour over top of cranberry mixture. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add egg yolks, beating one at a time, to creamed mixture.
Sift flour and soda three times; add alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla, coconut and nuts to creamed mixture.
Beat egg whites to peaks and fold into mixture.
Pour into three greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix together butter, cheese, flour, salt and red pepper.
Add ice water and knead together.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut in strips.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Bake in 300° oven until browned.
Sprinkle again with red pepper while hot.
Cool thoroughly before storing in airtight container.

title: mother's fudge
directions: Thoroughly combine dry ingredients in a heavy, 4-quart saucepan.
Stir in milk and bring to a bubbly boil on medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil, without stirring, to a soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Do not stir.
Cool at room temperature (110°).

title: crepes
directions: Beat all ingredients with rotary beater until smooth.
Grease a pan with butter.
Cook until light brown, like pancakes.
Turn and brown other side.
After, you can spread with jam, honey or sugar, or I put some apple or pineapple or peaches inside.

title: beary cherry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place stick of margarine in a 2 1/2-quart baking dish and melt in oven while preheating. Meanwhile, combine dry ingredients.
Stir in 3/4 cup milk (batter will be thin).
Pour batter into center of melted margarine.
Pour pie filling into center of batter.
Bake about 50 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Serve warm or cold with whipped cream.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter or margarine.
Mix sugar, flour and milk together. Stir until smooth.
Pour melted butter in dish that you are going to cook in.
Then put fruit in bottom.
Do not stir.
Cook in oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
You can use any kind of fruit (peaches, cherries, blackberries, etc.).

title: glazed lemonade cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Blend well, then beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Turn into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes, or until done. Prick cake with fork or skewer, completely through to bottom of cake.
Thoroughly blend lemonade concentrate and confectioners sugar.
Gradually spoon glaze over cake until completely absorbed. Cool and cut into squares.

title: apple butter stack cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together. Add eggs and beat well. Add flour, baking powder, soda and cinnamon. Then add buttermilk and vanilla. Mix well. This will be very thick and resemble cookie dough. Grease 8 cake pans. I used Pam spray and made 4 layers at a time. You can use either 8 or 9-inch pans. Divide the dough into 8 equal parts and then pat it into the pans.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a greased cake pan for 35 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: sweet-and-sour mustard
directions: In a saucepan, whisk together all ingredients.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Pour into small jars. Cover and refrigerate.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients. Grease and flour three (3 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch) pans.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken ball
directions: Mix cream cheese and chicken with hands.
Roll into big ball. Roll ball in bacon bits.
Place ball on cheese ball serving dish. Chill until firm.
Serve with Town House crackers.

title: lo-cal garlic chicken
directions: Mix garlic in with the Butter Buds.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Turn breasts 3 times.
Serves 4. Contains 150 calories per serving.

title: peach delight
directions: Stir lemon juice into peach pie filling.
Cut pie crust into strips.
Place filling in small casserole.
Place pie crust strips over.
Dot with butter; sprinkle with sugar.
Bake in 350° oven until crust is brown.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Dip eggplant in egg and then crumbs. Brown in hot oil.
Set aside.

title: sticky buns
directions: Thaw frozen bread, but do not let rise.
Sprinkle nuts in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, if desired.
Pinch sections of bread off and roll into balls about the size of quarters.
Roll the balls in the cinnamon-sugar mixture and place in pan.
Heat together the brown sugar, margarine, milk and pudding.
Pour the mixture over the dough balls.
Let the bread rise a couple of hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Invert immediately on a cookie sheet.

title: creamy broccoli bake
directions: Heat 1 inch salted water (1/2 teaspoon salt to 1 cup water) to boiling.
Add broccoli.
Cover and heat to boiling.
Cook until stems are almost tender, 10 to 12 minutes; drain.
Place broccoli in ungreased 1 1/2-quart round casserole.
Heat oven to 400°.
Beat soup and milk with hand beater until smooth; pour over broccoli. Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix baking mix and margarine until crumbly; sprinkle over cheese.
Bake until crumbs are light brown, about 20 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: enchiladas acapulco
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add tomato sauce and 1/2 cup green peppers.
Cook over medium heat 5 minutes stirring occasionally. Add beans and 1/4 pound cheese cubes.
Cook until cheese melts. Remove from heat.
Dip tortillas in hot oil; drain on paper towels.
Fill each tortilla with a 1/4 cup meat mixture, then roll up.
Place seam side down in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Pour remaining mixture over tortillas.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake 5 additional minutes to melt cheese.
Remove and top with remaining peppers, cheese and tomatoes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix and store in large container.
Use 1/4 cup mix in 1 cup hot water.

title: turkey surprise
directions: Brown turkey and drain any juices. Sprinkle flour over meat and mix well. Add sour cream and mushrooms. Cook over low heat until bubbly. Remove and serve with pasta. Serves 2 to 4.

title: sweet monkey bread
directions: Sprinkle pecans evenly in bottom of well-greased bundt pan.

title: play doh
directions: Mix ingredients and knead like dough.
Add food coloring if desired.
Store in airtight container.

title: skillet enchiladas
directions: In saucepan, combine
soup, enchiladas, sauce, milk and chilies; heat until bubbly.
Dip
tortillas, one at a time, in sauce until limp or place
in
warm skillet until limp.
Drain tortillas.	Set aside 1/2 cup cheese.
Place 1/4 cup cheese on each tortilla and roll.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together in bowl.
Chill until ready to serve.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: confetti salad
directions: Cook bows according to package directions; drain.
Rinse with cold water to cool quickly; drain well.
In large bowl, combine dressing, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Add cooked bows and remaining ingredients; toss lightly until pasta and vegetables are evenly coated.
Chill.
Makes 6 servings.

title: saturday night special
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Add pork and beans, tomatoes and salt. Pour half of mixture in baking dish, add layer of onions.
Add rest of mixture.

title: crock pot chili
directions: Cook ground beef, stirring to crumble. Add onion and the next 7 ingredients; cook for 7 minutes. Place in crock pot with beans and tomatoes; cook for 4 hours. Serve in bowls; top with cheese.

title: company spanish rice
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Add garlic, celery and beef; brown, stirring constantly.
Mix rice, tomatoes, tomato paste, salt, bay leaf and cayenne pepper with hot water.
Add to garlic and celery; stir well and cover.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and add beef bouillon.

title: grecco casserole
directions: Fry onion and pepper in small amount of oil until glossy. Brown meat.
Keep moving to prevent burning.
Add mushrooms and remove from heat.
Boil macaroni until tender; drain and add.
Add tomato sauce and corn; mix well.
Place in a well-greased casserole and refrigerate until ready to bake.
Grate lots of sharp Cheddar cheese on top.
Place in 300° oven for 1 hour.

title: aunt lucy's spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook hamburger, celery and onion until done.
Drain.
Then add rest of ingredients; bring to a boil, then simmer 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve over spaghetti noodles.

title: corn souffle
directions: Put cracker crumbs and milk in a greased casserole.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Mix well.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Bake in preheated oven (330°) for 50 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake another 10 minutes. Serves 4.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix and freeze first 6 ingredients.
Set out 1 to 1 1/2 hours before serving.
Pour ginger ale over and stir.
Ready to serve.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine chocolate chips and margarine and melt over low heat.
Stir until well blended.
Cool slightly. In mixing bowl, beat eggs with wire whisk until light (do not use electric mixer).
Beat in sugar and vanilla to chocolate mixture. Stir together flour, soda and salt.
Stir in egg mixture.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 45 minutes or until pulls away from edges of pan and sets in the center.
Cool completely before cutting into squares.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: tuna broccoli combo
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small casserole dish except cheese.
Top with cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Serves 1.

title: polish pierogi dough
directions: Mix flour, eggs, sour cream and salt.
Add a little water at a time until all is used.
Knead dough until firm and elastic texture.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350° or until lightly browned.
Cook in Pyrex or long pan.

title: barbecue shrimp
directions: Melt butter in olive oil.
Add all other ingredients, except shrimp.
Let sauce stand for 15 minutes.
When ready to cook, add shrimp and sauce to skillet and cook for 15 minutes, stirring often.
Divide shrimp into individual bowls.
Pour sauce over shrimp and serve with French bread for dipping.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat. Stir in vanilla, pineapple and finely chopped nuts; add bananas. Pour batter into 3 well-greased pans lined with wax paper.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool cake and ice with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: bean pot supper
directions: Brown hamburger, diced onion and bacon.
Simmer.
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer 2 hours.

title: quick chicken primavera
directions: Spray large skillet with Pam.
Heat, then add chicken and garlic.
Cook and stir until chicken is no longer pink, about 3 or 4 minutes.
Add milk and frozen vegetables with pasta.
Cover and simmer 4 to 8 minutes, or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Stir before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Pour into graham cracker crust or regular pie shell.
Freeze. Garnish with Hershey's chocolate syrup and peanuts.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter.
Mix brown sugar, butter, flour and eggs together.
Gradually add milk.
Pour into crusts and bake.
When top of pie starts to brown, turn oven down to 300° until pie is done.

title: chili #2
directions: Brown meat; drain fat.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: angel food dessert
directions: Bake the angel food cake according to the directions on the box.
Let cool.

title: zucchini and watercress soup
directions: Melt butter in large pot; saute onions.
Lower heat; cover. Stir occasionally until tender and lightly cover, 25 minutes.
Add broth.
Chop zucchini (trim ends).
Drop in broth.
Return to boil. Reduce heat until tender, 20 minutes.
Pull leaves and smaller stems off watercress.
Rinse well.
Remove soup from heat.
Add watercress.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Pour soup through strainer; reserve liquid.
Put solids in food processor.
Add 1 cup of liquid.
Process until smooth.
Return to pot and add about 2 more cups of liquid and/or* 1 cup cream and 1 cup liquid.
Season. Simmer to heat through.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Blend first 7 ingredients; carefully stir in blueberries. Sprinkle topping over batter and bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: fiddlehead salad(summer dish)
directions: Blanch carrots until fork tender.
Put the fiddleheads, carrots, onions, mushrooms and
cucumbers
in a big bowl.
Add dressing and toss together.
Best
to
let	set
4	or 5 hours before serving.

title: candied yams
directions: Wash yams.
Cover and bring to boil.
Boil for about 5 minutes.
Drain, peel and slice in half lengthwise.
Place the slices in a heavy 4-quart saucepan.
Add the sugar, spices, butter and boiling water.
Cook, uncovered, for 1 hour until the syrup has thickened and almost cooked away.
Turn the yams occasionally during the last half of the cooking time but do not stir.
Serve hot.

title: chili
directions: Cook and stir garlic and meat in a Dutch oven until meat loses its red color.
Add beans (if wanted) with their liquid.
Add onions and green pepper.
Pour in tomato sauce.
Add salt, cumin and chili powder.
Stir and simmer over low heat, stirring occasionally.

title: fruit kabobs
directions: You will need one (6-inch) wooden skewer.

title: christmas sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking soda and baking powder together in large mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening until mixture is crumbly, then beat in eggs and sour milk.
Add sugar and vanilla and mix well. Mixture will still feel rather dry.
Form about 1/3 of mixture into a ball and work with hands.
Place on floured board and roll out with rolling pin and cut into desired shapes.
Repeat with remaining dough.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° until dough starts to crack on top of cookie.
Ice if desired. These make great cookies for you to let your kids help make at Christmastime.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Heat juice and apples until apples are limp. Add remaining ingredients and cook 5 minutes.
Bake in double crust pie shell at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Cook frozen broccoli as directed.
Stir in 1/2 stick butter and the cheese.
Mix together 1/2 stick of butter and crushed Ritz crackers.
Sprinkle cracker mixture over broccoli and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and pour in baking dish.
Melt margarine; add corn flakes.
Mix and spread over potatoes.
Bake in medium oven until lightly browned.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown steak on medium heat slowly.
Transfer cooking pot to heating base using hot pads.
Combine ingredients, garlic, onion, salt, pepper, ginger, sugar and soy sauce.
Pour over steak. Cover; slow cook at setting #3 for 6 to 8 hours or setting #4 for 4 to 5 hours.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Take chicken broth and onion and cook until onion is clear in color.
Mix flour and cream and stir in gradually on low heat until bubbly.
Add in chicken, peas, mushrooms and pimento.
Cook until warm.
Serve on biscuit, rice or toast points.

title: 3 bean casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cook limas according to package; drain. Put in large casserole dish and add baked and kidney beans. Simmer sausage in small amount of water for 5 minutes in covered skillet.
Drain liquid and fry until brown.
(do not prick sausage, cut sausage into small pieces).
Add sausage and ham to beans.
Stir together other ingredients and pour over beans.
Mix gently.
Bake, uncovered, for approximately 1 hour.
Yields a lot.

title: baked potatoes
directions: Wash and slice potatoes but not all the way through.
Use the handle of a spoon to prevent knife from cutting all the way.
Put potatoes in baking dish and fan slightly.
Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle with herbs.
Bake at 425° for 50 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake additional 10 to 15 minutes until tender.

title: apple butter spice bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 5/8-inch loaf pan.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Set aside.
Sift and mix flour, baking powder, salt, baking soda and allspice.
Add to creamed mixture, alternating with apple butter and stir in nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes or until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove bread from pan; cool thoroughly before slicing.

title: bean soup
directions: Put beans in
large
kettle
filled
half
full of cold water; bring to a	boil.
Add
salt and salt pork.
Boil until tender, keeping kettle half full of water.

title: hot sauce
directions: Boil mixture.
Let cool.
Pour into sterilized bottles and cap.

title: spaghetti dip
directions: Combine sour cream, green pepper and dry sauce mix.
Chill and serve with vegetable dippers.

title: happiness cake
directions: Cream together and add 1 tablespoon each of neatness and ambition, a pinch of humor and enough temper to flavor.
Mix all thoroughly and add a generous quantity of love.
Place in the sunshine of a devoted husband's smile and the result will be a perfect wife and homemaker.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer in order given in a large bowl.
Refrigerate overnight, stirring just before serving.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook and drain carrots.
Let cool.
Mix together the other ingredients and pour over carrots.
Marinate 12 hours.
Serve cold.

title: whipping cream cake
directions: Mix ingredients in the order given.
Start cooking in a cold oven.
Bake at 350° until done.
Test for doneness.

title: muffin cones
directions: Mix muffin mix as directed.
Place the 10 cones in a muffin pan.
Cookie sheet can also be used.
Fill the cones with the batter approximately 1-inch from the cones' rims.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Test for doneness.
Decorate with yellow frosting and make "happy faces" with raisins, etc., or with a tube of chocolate icing.
Children can eat entire cone; contains no messy wrappers.

title: maggie's peach pie
directions: Pre-heat oven to 350 degrees.
While oven is heating, place margarine in 9x13 pan and place in oven.
Mix together flour, sugar, milk, vanilla, and cinnamon, until just combined.
Mixture will be lumpy.
Carefully add peaches and juice.
Mix well. Remove 9x13 pan from oven.
Carefully pour mixture into pan.
Return to oven till crust is brown, about 45 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: corn cakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add oil and egg and mix. Slowly stir in milk a little at a time until batter is the consistency of pancake mix.
Heat two tablespoons of bacon grease or oil in large skillet.
Drop batter by large spoonfuls into skillet and cook the same as pancakes.
Serve with butter and syrup.
Serves 8.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Mix ingredients as listed, with mixer.
Pour into pie shell. Refrigerate 2 hours before serving.

title: sally's easy lasagne
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat butter and sugars until creamy. Combine flour, baking soda and cinnamon; add to butter mixture. Stir in oats and raisins; mix well.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: spiced salad dressing
directions: Combine
all ingredients and blend well.
Makes about 1 (16 ounce) bottle.
A delicious treat with any of your salads.

title: smoked sausage and bean soup
directions: In a 4 quart Dutch oven, cook the onion and garlic in margarine or butter until tender, but not brown.
Add the water, potatoes, sausage, beans and bouillon granules.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat; simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.
Add cabbage or cole slaw mix, tomato paste or catsup and vinegar.
Simmer, covered, 10 minutes more.
Makes 6 main dish servings.

title: dorothy's pound cake
directions: Let butter soften.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour and whipping cream.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 1/2 hours.
(We check ours after 1 hour.)

title: uncooked tomato relish
directions: Soak 2 1/2
hours
in the 1/2 cup salt.
Mix sugar with vinegar and
place vegetables (chopped) in mixture.
Let stand for 2 hours. Fill jars with tops and keep refrigerated.

title: molded raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add berries and stir until thawed. Add pineapple, then bananas.
Pour half the mixture into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Spread on sour cream.
Add remaining mixture.
Refrigerate.
For best results, make day before serving.
For Christmas, color sour cream green and have red and green salad.

title: pan coating
directions: Mix ingredients to smoothness and store in covered container on pantry shelf.

title: squash bisque
directions: Cook all of ingredients until tender.
Run through food mill or puree in blender until very creamy in texture.
If soup is too thick at this point, add more chicken broth or milk.
Garnish with croutons or other seasonings to taste.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add melted butter, eggs and vanilla.
Mix with a fork and add chopped pecans.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes in buttered square glass pan.

title: basque skillet dinner
directions: Cut turkey sausage into bite-sized pieces and brown in skillet.
Add onion and pepper and cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 30 to 45 minutes.

title: italian olive bread
directions: Mix butter and mayo together and melt.
Spread over each slice of bread.
Chop olives and layer on bread.
Grate cheese and layer.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: dutch meat loaf
directions: Mix these ingredients and pour over the meat loaf in the oven. Continue baking 1 1/4 hours longer, basting occasionally.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hildy's cheese strada with ham and broccoli
directions: Cut 12 doughnuts and holes from the slices of white bread. Fit the resulting scraps of bread (crust removed) in the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Layer sliced cheese, cooked and drained broccoli and ham over the bread.
Arrange doughnuts and holes on the top, with doughnuts down the sides and holes in the middle.
Combine slightly beaten eggs, milk, onion, salt and mustard; pour over bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 55 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: apple raisin cookies
directions: Cream together Parkay, egg and brown sugar.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Add apples, pecans and raisins by hand.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheets.
It is better to let mixture set before baking so apples have a chance to mix, about 15 minutes, then stir good.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Frost with cream cheese frosting or plain vanilla frosting.

title: health bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 (1 pound) shortening cans or other 2 1/2-cup cans.
There are small (2 1/2 cup) loaf pans.
Mix all ingredients, except 1 tablespoon wheat germ, and the water in a medium size bowl.
Stir in water until just blended.
Spoon into cans, smooth top and sprinkle with remaining wheat germ.
Bake until tops are golden brown and pick inserted in center comes out clean.
As soon as out of oven, remove from cans and put in zip-lock bags.
Great with split pea soup.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all well. Chill and serve.

title: cake and pie filling
directions: Pour oil into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread on bottom of pan. Put cake mix, eggs and water into pan.
Stir until blended, about 2 minutes.
Spoon pie filling into batter to create a marble effect.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: scotch tea tarts
directions: Mix butter, flour and cream cheese; chill for 30 minutes. Place a rounded teaspoonful of dough in each tart cup.
Press dough to bottom and sides with thumb.
Sprinkle each cup with chopped pecans.
Mix the brown sugar, eggs, melted butter, salt and vanilla together.
Spoon in the cups, over top of the pecans. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream the margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add beaten eggs, vanilla and milk.
Blend together in another bowl the flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Stir into egg mixture; blend thoroughly.
Wrap in waxed paper (better in small packages). Store in refrigerator at least 3 hours.
Roll out on floured board; cut into shapes.
Decorate with colored sugar, nuts, raisins, etc.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: anginettes (italian cookies)
directions: Cut together with a pastry blender the flour and butter.
Stir in the sugar and baking powder.
Add to this mixture, eggs, milk, lemon juice and zambucca.
Form dough and chill 1/2 hour.
Roll into ropes and tie in knots.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes. Ice with the following.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Stir in pineapple and bread.
Bake in ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix in pan the sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine.
Put on medium heat and bring to a rolling boil and boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Quickly add vanilla, salt and peanut butter. Stir.
Add oatmeal. Stir well. Drop by teaspoonful onto wax paper. Let cool, then remove from paper.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Combine and mix well. Pour into a hot greased skillet and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: homemade grape juice
directions: Mix grapes and sugar; pour into a 1/2 gallon jug.
Fill with water.
Cook in pressure cooker for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: italian chocolate cookies
directions: Soak raisins in rum for a day (the longer, the better). Mix all ingredients well. Roll into small balls. Place on a greased cookie sheet. Bake 18 to 25 minutes at 350.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Stir together peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt in 1 1/2-quart casserole. Microwave on HIGH for 7 to 8 minutes, stirring well after 3 minutes. Add butter and vanilla to syrup, blending well. Microwave on HIGH for 1 to 2 minutes more. Peanuts will be lightly browned and syrup very HOT. Add baking soda and gently stir until light and foamy. Pour mixture onto lightly greased cookie sheet; let cool 30 minutes to 1 hour. When cool, break into small pieces and store in airtight container.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Break cauliflower into flowerets.
Combine Parmesan cheese and mayonnaise.
Toss all ingredients except bacon together. Refrigerate 6 to 8 hours.
Add bacon just before serving.
Serves 8.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mash potatoes.
Melt butter and add to potatoes.
Add sugar and salt.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, or all together.
Beat until smooth.
Add milk and beat again until smooth.
Lastly, add spices.
Pour into 4 to 5 pie shells (4 full or 5 medium-full pies).
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes until browned.

title: vegetable soup(ukrainian)
directions: Cook the onion in the butter until slightly wilted.
Add the vegetables, soup stock and water.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Add the tomato juice.
Blend the flour with the cream; add some hot soup to it and stir into the contents of the kettle. Bring to a boil.
Season to taste with the salt and pepper and flavor with the parsley or dill.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients (corn meal, sugar, salt, flour and baking powder).
Add the egg, milk, salad oil, corn and cottage cheese; stir lightly.
Pour half of batter into a 9-inch square casserole (well-greased).
Add the cheese and peppers.
Pour rest of batter over this.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes, until golden on top.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: broccoli mushroom chowder
directions: Clean and cut broccoli into 1/2-inch pieces.
Steam in 1/2 cup water until tender.
Do not drain.
Set aside.
Wash and slice mushrooms.
Melt butter in saucepan over medium heat.
Add flour to make a roux.
Cook for 2 to 4 minutes.
Add chicken stock, stirring with a wire whip, and bring to a boil.
Turn heat to low. Add broccoli, mushrooms, half and half and spices.
Heat but do not boil.

title: egg pie crust
directions: Measure flour and salt into bowl.
Add shortening.
Mix with pastry cutter (or two table knives) until crumbly.
Add egg water in small amounts, mixing with spoon.
Makes six 8-inch crusts.

title: grandma carter's jello salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: chicken croquettes
directions: Stir all together and put hot butter in frying pan and add onions, milk and flour to prepare a creamy sauce, when done add chicken.
Put in the refrigerator for 3 hours.
Afterward give form of croquettes and mix them with eggs and crushed crackers and fry them.

title: tortilla rolls
directions: Mix cream cheese, Cheddar cheese, finely chopped green onions, paprika and bacon bits. Spread mixture thinly on tortilla and roll up. Refrigerate until ready to serve. Slice into half-inch thickness and serve.

title: salted peanut chews
directions: Combine all crust ingredients, except marshmallows, at low speed until crumbly.
Press firmly in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with marshmallows.
Bake 1 to 2 minutes more, until marshmallows begin to puff.
Cool.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Butter light bread on both sides and line bottom of casserole dish.
Beat eggs and milk.
Sprinkle sausage over bread.
Pour egg mixture over sausage and bread. Spread cheese over this and refrigerate overnight.
Bake 35 minutes in 350° oven.
Can be frozen unbaked for up to 2 months.

title: "chicken excellent"
directions: Place chicken in shallow baking pan.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover with foil and refrigerate at least 3 hours.
When ready to bake, spoon sauce over chicken and bake at 375° for 1 1/4 hours, covered with foil.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat eggs 5 minutes on high speed.
Gradually add sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Stir.
Add flour, baking powder, etc.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Beat egg slightly with fork.
Stir in milk.
Add salad oil or butter.
Sift together and add flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir just until flour is moistened.
Batter should be lumpy.
Do not overmix.
Put in blueberries.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Can use cupcake pan.

title: terri's meat loaf
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients all together, then stir in crackers. Shape meat in baking dish.
Cover with ketchup.
Pour reserved juice from tomatoes around meat loaf.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.
Reduce temperature to 325°.
Pour 1 cup brown gravy or cajun gravy (from mix) around meat loaf.
Bake another 30 to 40 minutes.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Mix pecan halves or English walnut halves into beaten egg white and water.
Mix all until well coated.
Then, put into sugar and spice mixture and mix until sugar is gone.
Spread nuts on greased cookie sheet and bake at 250°.
Stir every 15 minutes for 1 hour.
Cool on waxed paper, then separate nuts.

title: country chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a large skillet, over medium heat, heat 2 tbsp. oil.
Add chicken and saute 4-5 minutes on each side until golden brown.
Remove and set aside.
Add remaining oil and flour to skillet and cook, stirring for about 3 minutes, until golden.
Add chicken broth and mustard.
Cook, stirring, until sauce is smooth and thick.
Season with salt and pepper.
Stir in vegetables.
Shred chicken and add to vegetables.

title: cocktail franks
directions: Mix and heat until warm.

title: yam muffins
directions: Rinse
raisins	and
pecans
in boiling water.	Mix all ingredients together and bake in greased muffin pans.
(Papers may be used in the pan.) Batter may be baked as loaf bread or a pancake.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mrs. early's spinach salad
directions: Mix together and let marinate.
The bacon bits, croutons and chopped eggs are optional.
You may also prefer to go a little lighter on the dressing.
One-half of the package may be plenty for some tastes.
Serves four to six.

title: christmas jam
directions: In large pan, combine apricots, pineapple and syrup, water and cherry syrup.
Let stand 1 hour, then cook slowly until apricots are tender.
Add sugar; cook slowly, stirring often, until thick (216°).
Cut cherries in quarters; add and cook a few minutes longer.
Pour into hot, sterilized jars and seal.
Makes 6 1/2 pints.

title: sangria
directions: Combine and let stand 15 to 20 minutes.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown meat. Add onion and tomato sauce. Season to taste.
Set aside.
Line a large dish with corn tortillas.
Add tamales. Add half of the meat on top of the tamales (may split tamales lengthways, if desired).
Make second layer of corn tortillas, tamales and meat.
Place grated cheese on top. Add approximately 10 ounces water to dish. Cover with foil, loosely.
Cook at 300° to 350° for about 15 to 20 minutes until cheese melts evenly. Uncover and cook for about 5 or 10 minutes more.
You may serve with picante sauce as desired.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Soak oatmeal in buttermilk for 1 hour.
Add egg and beat well. Add sugar and milk.
Add flour, sifted with salt, powder and soda. Add cooled shortening.
Bake in greased muffin pans in 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: southern date nut cake
directions: Combine nuts and dates; mix well.
Add flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Continue to mix well.
Use your hands to mix evenly.
Beat eggs in a bowl.
Add vanilla and chopped cherries. Mix with hands to work the batter thoroughly.
The mixture will seem a little dry.
Grease and flour a tube pan generously.
Line the bottom with wax paper.
Pack mixture into the tube pan and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: mock chow mein
directions: Fry hamburger and diced onion; drain off fat.
Mix raw rice, soups and hamburger in covered baking dish.
Add mushrooms; do not drain juice.
Put in with mixture; add soy sauce to taste.
Mix about 4 cans of water into mixture.
Add celery.
Bake at 350° until rice is done.
Add more water if needed to finish cooking rice.
Stir mixture every 1/2 hour.

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: In medium bowl, beat the cream cheese until light and fluffy. Slowly add sweetened condensed milk; beat until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla until well mixed.
Pour into crust.
Chill 3 hours, until firm, then top with cherry pie filling.

title: pita pizzas
directions: Individual pizzas:
Arrange pita bread (whole) on cookie sheet. Spoon on pizza sauce.
Then arrange toppings on bread.
Place cookie sheet in oven preheated to 400°.
Cook pizzas for 15 to 18 minutes or until cheese has melted.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Thinly slice cucumbers; add onions, peppers and whole garlic cloves. Add salt. Cover with cracked ice; mix thoroughly. Let stand 3 hours. Drain well. Combine remaining ingredients. Pour over cucumber mixture. Heat just to boil; seal in hot sterilized jars. Makes 5 pints.

title: spinach vegetable dip
directions: Mix well.
Let stand overnight.
Use as a dip for a vegetable tray.

title: fried ice cream
directions: Take one scoop of ice cream and form into ball.
Make as many as needed.
Put them into freezer until hard.
Mix crumbs, sugar and cinnamon together.
Take ice cream balls from freezer and roll in mixture, pressing into ice cream.
Have deep fryer ready with Crisco oil as hot as you would have for French fries.
Put ice cream ball on slotted spoon and dip down in oil and right back out.
Beat bottom of spoon lightly on paper towel, then put ball in a sherbet dish.
Top with whipped cream and a maraschino cherry and serve.

title: chicken noodles
directions: Boil chicken; take meat off bones.
Cook egg noodles.
Mix chicken and noodles in baking dish with cream of mushroom soup. Put shredded Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 375° until cheese melts or is hot.
Serve with mashed potatoes and corn.

title: adam's different vegetable soup
directions: Brown the meat; drain. Pour into a large pot with rest of ingredients. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour. It is very aromatic while cooking and tastes as good as it smells.

title: cream cheese pineapple pie
directions: Drain
syrup from pineapple chunks and add enough water to make
1 cup.
Chill chunks.
Bring syrup to a boil and stir slowly into
lemon
jello.
When dissolved, stir half of this jello mixture
into
softened
cream cheese.
When smooth and thoroughly blended,place this mixture in crumb crust and chill thoroughly.

title: savory italian rice bake(8 servings)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare rice as package directs.
Crumble and brown sausage and onions.
Drain and reserve 1 tablespoon drippings.
Saute zucchini and garlic 3 minutes until crisp-tender.
Combine rice, sausage and 1 1/2 cups spaghetti sauce and basil.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with half of cheese.
Top with zucchini and then remaining sauce and then rest of cheese.
Bake 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: lutheran chicken
directions: Melt butter in large skillet and brown chicken pieces. Remove chicken and add vegetables to skillet.
Brown lightly.

title: pear amber
directions: Wash oranges; cut up and remove seeds, then dice or grind coarsely, peeling and all.
Add drained pineapple and peeled and diced pears to orange mixture.
(The orange and pineapple mixture keeps the pears from getting dark.)
Measure this mixture into a large, broad kettle.
For each cup, add 3 cups of sugar.
Heat slowly to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil, stirring frequently, 20 to 30 minutes longer, until pears are transparent and mixture is as thick as you like.
Add cherries.
Remove from heat; let stand overnight.
Stir occasionally while cooling.
Heat to boil; pack into jars.
Makes 3 1/2 pints.

title: spice tea
directions: Use 2 tablespoons to 1 cup hot water (or to taste).

title: "tom's" blonde brownies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Melt margarine in saucepan; add sugar.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture gradually.
Mix well.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch (lightly greased) pan.
Sprinkle with chips and nuts.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Cut in bars.
Makes 48. Great for tailgate parties!

title: banana roll
directions: Peel and cut bananas in half lengthwise or slice.
Spread with peanut butter.
Roll in coconut and chill until served.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pat valley's hot pepper jelly
directions: Mix peppers, sugar and vinegar.
Bring to a boil for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add color and Certo.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat egg.
Add other ingredients and beat well.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 375°.
Cook until browned and a knife inserted comes out clean (about 1 hour).
Turn oven down to finish cooking if it browns too much.

title: shantell's favorite snack
directions: Mix the onion soup mix into the sour cream.
Stir well.
Place on crackers and eat.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In small mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar until fluffy.
Add peanut butter and beat well.
Gradually beat in milk. Fold in topping.
Pile into pie shell.
Sprinkle with peanuts. Freeze until firm, then wrap in moisture proof wrap.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Add half of the hash browns.
Mix soup, sour cream, milk and onions.
Pour half of the mixture over the potatoes.
Spread cheese over mixture. Spread remaining soup mixture, cheese and 2 tablespoons butter on top of the corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Beat milk and pudding mix until thick; add Cool Whip.
Spread half of the pudding mixture over the graham crackers.
Add another layer of graham crackers.
Add the remaining pudding on top of the second layer.
Add third layer of graham crackers.

title: hot chicken salad oriental
directions: In bowl, stir together first 4 ingredients until blended. Stir in chicken, celery, water chestnuts and onion.
Add macaroni; toss to coat well.
Spoon into 2-quart casserole.
Top with chow mein noodles.
Bake in 375° oven 20 to 25 minutes or until heated. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: hamburger steak pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onions in oil.
Add potatoes, carrots, seasonings, and water; simmer gently 20 minutes or until vegetables are soft.
Pour into a deep casserole and cover with short biscuit crust (according to package) and bake until crust is brown (about 25 minutes) in hot oven at 400°.
My mom usually makes this as a two crust pie instead of using biscuit dough.

title: christmas bread
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar, butter and salt, cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast mixture and 3 cups flour.
Let rise 1 hour, then add vanilla and eggs.
Mix fruit and raisins with 1/4 cup flour, add to dough, then add enough flour to handle (about 4 cups).
Knead well and let rise until light.
Put in greased loaf pans.
Let rise until doubled.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake about 40 minutes.
Frost with confectioners sugar.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: prune nut bread
directions: Drain prunes; save liquid.
Add enough water to make 1/2 cup liquid.
Combine with buttermilk; set aside.
Mix flour, baking soda, baking powder and wheat flour.
Combine prunes, nuts and 1 cup of dry ingredients.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine egg, milk, 2/3 cup cracker crumbs, 1/4 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Stir in corn, onion and pimento; mix well. Turn into a 1 quart casserole.
Toss butter with remaining crumbs; sprinkle on top of corn mixture.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven 1 hour or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: "hot dog" casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare potato puffs for 4 servings as directed on package.
Stir pickle relish, mayonnaise, onion and mustard.
Spoon into ungreased 1-quart casserole dish.
Cut each frankfurter lengthwise in half, then cut crosswise in half. Insert frankfurter pieces upright around edge of mashed potatoes. Bake, uncovered, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese balls(they're really good!)
directions: Unwrap crescent dinner roll dough.
Cut each individual triangle into three equal triangles.
Wrap around cocktail wiener, leaving seam at bottom.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Lay pork chops in 2-quart casserole.
Put a slice of onion on each.
Sprinkle with a few drops of lemon juice and a small teaspoon of brown sugar.
Put a few drops of ketchup on each one. Repeat in layers until all chops are used.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: homemade fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and salt together in a large saucepan.
Add milk, stir well.
Bring to a boil; do not stir again until fudge comes to a soft ball at bottom of a cold cup of water.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla extract.
Beat with electric beater until smooth and thick (takes about 5 minutes).
Put on a greased (with butter) cookie sheet.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: baked chicken
directions: Wash chicken.
Dip in flour, then egg mixture.
Dip in bread crumbs with a little Parmesan cheese mixed in.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to one hour.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta; drain well.
Add salad dressing and Salad Supreme; marinate overnight in the refrigerator.
Next day, add tomatoes, pepper and cucumber.

title: strawberry snow cake
directions: Cut cake in half. Tear into small pieces and spread on bottom of glass or metal dish. Mix Dream Whip as directed. Add powdered sugar and cream cheese to Dream Whip. Mix well. Spread over broken pieces of cake. Tear other half of cake and place on top of that. Mix strawberries in glaze and spread over cake. Cool in refrigerator.

title: parsley rice
directions: Saute onion and garlic in melted butter; add to rice.
Beat egg and milk.
Add egg mixture, grated cheese and chopped parsley to rice mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place sliced apples in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend remaining ingredients until crumbly; spread over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until apples are tender and topping is golden brown.
Serve warm with cream or ice cream.
Serves 12.

title: creole style green beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon, saving 3 tablespoons drippings.
Cook onion and green pepper in this until tender. Blend in flour, sugar and seasonings.
Add tomatoes and cook until thickened.
Add beans.
Heat thoroughly.
Put in casserole and sprinkle with diced bacon.
Keep warm in oven.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Pour in 9-inch pie shell and bake for 1 1/2 hours in 300° oven.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat butter, sugars, egg and vanilla together.
Mix flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Stir into sugar mixture (mix well).
Stir in coconut and corn flakes.
Drop by teaspoon on baking sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until lightly browned.
Cool slightly.
Remove from pan to cooling rack.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: tea
directions: In heated tea pot, pour boiled water over tea bags, cinnamon, cloves, orange juice and brown sugar.
Let steep 3 to 4 minutes. Serves 4.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook chicken and pull from bones.
Cook together beef, pork and onion in 1 cup chicken stock and just enough water to cover meat.
Cook slowly for 1 hour.
Salt to taste.
Add catsup and tomatoes; cook another hour.
Add corn, chicken and 1 teaspoon ground red pepper.
Cook slowly another hour and stir often. (Three hours cooking time.)

title: heavenly cake
directions: Bake cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan, according to box directions. When done, poke holes in cake.
While cake is cooling, combine pineapple and sugar.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Pour over cake while hot.
Let stand until cool; then prepare pudding mix according to box directions.
Spread over cake.
Spread whipped cream topping over this.
Refrigerate.

title: orange jello, orange sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups of boiling water.
Add orange sherbet.
Let set partially and add whipped cream and mandarin oranges.
Put in mold and let set.
(Drain mandarin oranges well.)

title: tomato, mozzarella, red onion salad
directions: Clean and dry tomatoes; cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Peel and cut red onions into 1/4-inch slices.
Slice cheese lengthwise thinly using knife or cheese slicer.
Arrange tomatoes, onions and cheese circularly around platter, one layer on top of the next. Drain can of olives and pour olives evenly over platter.
Season with salt, pepper and parsley.
Add fresh basil leaves over the platter in layers or in pieces.
Drizzle olive oil and vinegar to taste over platter.
Refrigerate after covering with plastic wrap. Serve cold with fresh Italian bread.

title: phyllis's pimiento cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.

title: stir-fry chicken fajitas
directions: In heavy plastic bag, combine chicken strips and dressing. Refrigerate for several hours or overnight, turning bag occasionally.
Drain.
Heat a 12-inch nonstick skillet over medium-high heat; stir-fry chicken strips and onions for 2 minutes.
Add pepper strips and mushrooms; cook and stir until chicken is done and peppers are tender-crisp.
Season with garlic salt, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Serve in warm tortillas.
Top with picante sauce and sour cream.
(Also, fresh chopped tomatoes if in season.)

title: zucchini cakes
directions: Combine grated zucchini, beaten egg and melted margarine.
Add seasoned bread crumbs, onion and Old Bay and mix well.
Shape into patties.
Broil.

title: baked seasoned potatoes
directions: Spread diced potatoes (peelings optional) in shallow baking dish.
Pour melted margarine over potatoes.
Sprinkle seasonings evenly over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Test for doneness.
Stir before serving.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Put potato chips on top (crushed).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Pour all ingredients into a large pan.
Mix well, at this point only add about 1/2 gallon milk.
After mixing is complete, place on stove and warm to insure everything is dissolved.
Once warmed, pour everything in ice cream freezer.
Add remaining milk to fill line on freezer.
Freeze in ice cream freezer until frozen; then pack freezer with ice for an hour to insure it is good and frozen.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients and put in a 9 x 12-inch Pyrex dish. Add a little chicken broth if mixture seems dry.
Mix crushed chips and cheese and place on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: no weep meringue
directions: Boil water, salt, cornstarch and vanilla until it is clear. Cool.
Add sugar and 3 egg whites that have been stiffly beaten. Beat into cooked mixture.
Put on top of pie; brown at 350°.

title: warm spinach 'n cheddar dip
directions: In 1-quart casserole dish, combine vegetable recipe soup mix, sour cream, spinach and 3/4 cup cheese until smooth.
Top with remaining 1/4 cup cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes about 3 cups dip.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Arrange red leaf lettuce on individual salad plates.
Place either red or white onion slices, alternately, with grapefruit slices, which have been peeled and all pith removed.
Mayonnaise or any fruit dressing may be used.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and meal.
Add eggs.
Beat until creamy.
Add butter, milk and lemon juice and rind.
Beat until smooth.
Put in unbaked pie crusts.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: peach delight
directions: Note:
Prepare in an 11 x 7-inch pan.

title: cheese ball
