title: strawberry tapioca salad
directions: Boil water, add tapioca and simmer with lid for 25 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add sugar and dry jello.
Cool.
Add frozen strawberries and Cool Whip.
Pour in bowl and refrigerate.

title: stir-fry minced chicken with vegetables
directions: Cut chicken breasts into cube size, then add soy sauce, cornstarch and cooking wine and soak for a while.
Meanwhile, cut green peppers, celery, water chestnuts, carrots, bamboo shoots and onions into cube size.
Stir-fry chicken in 3 tablespoons oil for 3 minutes; remove to a bowl.
Heat the other 3 tablespoons oil to fry onions, bamboo shoots, water chestnuts, celery, carrots and green peppers.
Then add chicken to the pan.
Mix well.

title: italian carbonara
directions: Brown bacon and drain.
Saute ham and garlic in a little butter.
Add all ingredients except eggs.
Mix well.
Turn off the heat and pour eggs over and quickly toss to coat spaghetti mixture.
Add olives.

title: three bean salad
directions: Combine vegetables, salt and pepper.
Mix oil, sugar and vinegar together
and pour over vegetables.
Allow to set a few hours.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in greased pans at 400° until brown, about 35 minutes.

title: pineapple topping (to be used on cakes)
directions: Cook until it looks clear. This topping is great between layers of white or yellow cake. Then top with Cool Whip or make a cream cheese icing for the top.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Mix soup and milk well.
Cook the chicken with celery and onion (salt and pepper).
Take off the bone.
Save the liquid, celery and onion.
Put chicken into a large Pyrex dish.
Pour mushroom soup, chicken soup and milk mixture over chicken.
Mix Pepperidge Farm stuffing (using liquid, celery and onion).
Mix the dressing according to directions.
Put dressing on top of mushroom mixture. Bake about 1 hour at 325°.
Homemade dressing can be used.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Saute together green pepper, onion and oil for 5 minutes.
Mix Italian seasoning and garlic powder, then add to pepper, onion and oil mixture.
Add cottage cheese and egg whites to chopped spinach and mix with shredded Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.

title: speedy pizza
directions: Put salt and pepper and flour it real good.
Then put oil in pan and fry until it's done.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil and sugar.
Mix well.
Add grated zucchini and vanilla; mix.
Add flour and dry ingredients.
Then add nuts or raisins.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: low-fat berry pie
directions: To pre-bake crust:
Preheat oven to 375°.
Place foil or waxed paper over crust, weight it down with dried beans or grains.
Bake for 15 minutes, remove foil and beans and bake 10 more minutes until lightly browned.
Remove from oven and cool completely. Place about 2 cups berries in food processor.
Add 1/3 cup sugar and puree.
Taste to adjust sugar; set aside.
Place remaining berries in the cooled crust and gently spread into place.
Put cornstarch into small saucepan and whisk in pureed berries.
Bring to boil, then lower heat and simmer, whisking frequently, until thickened (5 minutes).
Remove from heat and pour over berries in the crust.
Cool to room temperature or chill before serving.

title: pizza sticks
directions: Separate and unroll breadsticks.

Place 3 pepperoni slices in single layer over 1/2 of each breadstick. Fold remaining half of breadstick over top; seal end and twist. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Combine cheese, Italian seasoning and garlic powder. Sprinkle evenly over each breadstick.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown. Serve with pizza sauce.
Makes 8 pizza sticks.

title: eggplant with mac nuts
directions: Halve each eggplant and scoop out the pulp, leaving a 1/4-inch thick shell.
Dice the pulp finely.
Heat oil in a skillet and cook onion and garlic in it until tender.
Add eggplant pulp and cook slowly until lightly browned and almost tender.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add tomato and Worcestershire and simmer 3 minutes.
Stir in eggs and nuts and use to stuff eggplant shells. Top with bread crumbs.
Set in an oiled shallow roasting pans. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until shells are tender.
Serves 6.

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Blend soup and milk in large bowl.
Stir in cheese, onions, macaroni and beef.
Fold in eggs, if using. Pour mixture into ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover tightly. Bake 30 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate oatmeal cake
directions: Pour first two ingredients together and let stand for 10 minutes. Add rest of ingredients. Place in a greased 9x13 pan and bake 350 degrees for 25 minutes. This is a very moist and delicious cake it can be topped with a sprinkle of powdered sugar instead of frosting.

title: parmesan eggplant spaghetti sauce
directions: Heat oil in Dutch oven over medium heat.
Cook and stir eggplant, onion, garlic and parsley in oil until onion is tender, about 8 minutes.
Stir in the rest of the ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, 15 minutes.
Put on spaghetti and top with Parmesan cheese.

title: meatless chili
directions: Heat oil in a 6-quart pot.
Saute onion until brown.
Add beans, tomatoes, celery, ketchup, dry mustard and pepper.
Add chili to taste.
Simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
Can be frozen.
Serves 8.
Calories: 265.
Fat: 3 gm.
Chol. 0.

title: jam bars
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream together shortening, sugar, vanilla and flavoring.
Add egg.
Sift together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, cloves and salt.
Add to first mixture and blend well.
Spread half in a buttered 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Cover with layer of jam or jelly.
Pat rest of dough on top.
Bake 25 minutes.
Cool.
Cut in bars.
Makes about 20.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish. Dump ingredients in dish in order (cherry pie filling, undrained pineapple, dry cake mix and nuts).
Smooth after each layer; do not mix.
Place the butter pieces on top.
Bake for 1 hour.
Serve with ice cream.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well by hand.
Put into pan and refrigerate at least 1 hour before cutting.

title: apricot salad
directions: Prepare
jello according to directions on box.	When it starts to
congeal,
add pineapple, bananas and marshmallows. Refrigerate while making topping.

title: hot pimiento dip
directions: Combine mayonnaise, cheese, olives, pimientos and garlic in small baking dish.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 minutes.

title: mabel hill's peanut chip cookies
directions: Cream all ingredients except peanuts and chips.
Add peanuts and chips; mix well.
Drop on cookie sheet and bake 9 minutes at 350°.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix gelatine, sugar and salt thoroughly in a small saucepan. Add 1/2 cup of the water and place over low heat, stirring constantly until gelatine is dissolved.
Remove from heat and stir in remaining 1 cup of water and vinegar or lemon juice.
Chill mixture to unbeaten egg white consistency.
Fold in diced apples, chopped celery and chopped nuts.
Turn into a 4 cup mold or individual molds and chill until firm.
Unmold by slipping mold in warm water to the depth of the gelatine.
Loosen around edge with tip of a knife.
Place serving dish on mold and turn upside down. Shake holding serving dish on mold turned upside down.
Shake holding serving dish tightly to mold.
Garnish with fruit.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add hot applesauce.
Mix and sift dry ingredients and spices.
Add to the applesauce mixture.
Add nuts and chopped dates or raisins.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 375° 20-30 minutes.

title: ume pasta
directions: Put
salt
and pasta in boiling water.
Cook until well done. Drain
pasta.
While pasta is still hot, add butter and Umeboshi. Mix
until
butter
is completely melted.
Decorate with parsley.

title: marshmallow waldorf salad
directions: Mix apples, marshmallows, grapes, celery, walnuts and enough mayonnaise to moisten.
Refrigerate.

title: taco dip
directions: In pizza pan spread refried beans.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning until smooth.
Pour over beans and spread.
Dice tomatoes, green peppers and olives.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Serve with taco chips.

title: syrup cake
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan; bake at 350° until done.

title: ashville salad
directions: Heat soup and cheese until melted.
Add gelatin and stir until smooth.
Cool a bit, then add mayonnaise and vegetables.

title: homemade sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth. Store in refrigerator, covered.
Makes 8 ounces.
Use as you would Eagle Brand milk.

title: lime pickles
directions: Prepare lime solution with the 5 quarts water and the hydrated lime.
Wash cucumbers thoroughly and slice.
Soak cucumbers in lime solution for 24 hours.
Wash cucumbers in several waters to remove lime.

title: cottage cheese delight
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl and chill overnight in refrigerator.

title: yellow buns
directions: Cook milk and corn meal until thick.
Add butter, sugar and salt.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and let stand for 20 minutes; then add eggs and flour.
Combine with corn meal mixture and add enough additional flour (3 to 3 1/2 cups) to make a soft bun dough.
Knead on floured board.
Set covered in a warm place.
Let rise until full size.
Punch down and let rise again.
Then form into buns.
Rise and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix green beans & corn, put in greased casserole dish.
Mix soup, sour cream, cheese, onions and salt, spread over beans and corn.
Mix melted butter with cracker crumbs & almonds.
Spread over casserole.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325° uncovered.
Can be mixed & refrigerated over night before baking.

title: watergate salad
directions: Sprinkle dry Jell-O over all other ingredients and add Cool Whip.
One-half cup of chopped pecans may be added.

title: "grilled" or "broiled" teriyaki chops(serves 4)
directions: Whisk together all ingredients, except chops.
Marinate chops in mixture in refrigerator for 1 to 2 hours.
Remove.
Broil or grill chops for 12 to 15 minutes.
Brush with marinade; turn once.

title: old-fashioned applesauce cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease well and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt and spices into large bowl of electric mixer.
Add shortening and applesauce; beat 1 minute at low speed, just to combine.
At medium speed, beat 2 minutes, constantly cleaning side of bowl with rubber scraper and guiding batter into beaters.
Add eggs; beat 2 minutes. Combine raisins and walnuts; fold into batter with rubber scraper. Turn batter into prepared pan.
Bake 45 minutes, or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cake cool completely in pan on wire rack.
Frost as desired.
To serve, cut into rectangles.

title: bean-pea casserole
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, Durkee, mustard, cooking oil, Worcestershire sauce and boiled eggs.
Put mixture in beans and peas and mix well.
Heat in 375° oven until bubbly.
Add French onions.
Return to oven until onions are warmed.

title: mississippi fudge cake
directions: Melt the butter and add the first four
ingredients together. Mix well.
Stir in 1 1/2 c. chopped nuts.
Bake 30 minutes on 350°. After cake is done, place marshmallows on top of hot cake and place back in oven to toast lightly.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Let this set up before adding second layer.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Cover hamburger with water and break into bits.
Add celery and onion and any other veggie you wish.
Potatoes tend to mush up.
Add can of beef broth and water to cover contents.
Add seasoning, salt, pepper and garlic salt, if you prefer.
Put in crock-pot.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Skim any fat next day. Reheat and eat.
Makes a thick soup.

title: crustless south of the border quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Butter a 10 x 15 x 2-inch baking pan. In large bowl, beat eggs until slightly thickened; add flour and baking powder and blend well.
Add Jack cheese, Cheddar cheese, cottage cheese, chiles and butter; stir until smooth.
Pour into prepared pan and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Lower heat to 350° and continue to bake for 45 minutes or until quiche is set and lightly golden on top.
Allow to cool slightly, cut into 1 1/2-inch squares and serve hot or at room temperature.

title: no roll sugar cookies
directions: In large bowl, cream sugar, powdered sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add oil, vanilla and eggs; mix well. Stir in flour, baking soda, cream of tartar and salt until well blended.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight for easier handling.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix butter, sugar and eggs in large bowl.
Add dry ingredients (sift together).
Combine, using heavy spoon or hands.
Add nuts, fruit and flavoring.
Bake 1 pound loaves at 275° for 2 hours and tube pan at 275° for 3 hours.
Half hour before done, take out of oven and brush with honey and corn syrup.
Continue baking.
Turn upside down to cool.
Wrap in a wine cloth.
Store in a plastic bag in a cool place.

title: fruit crisps
directions: Cut butter into dry ingredients until crumbly.
Press mixture over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: mincemeat
directions: Chop oranges, raisins, apples and cherries and put in large kettle.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Then simmer and stir occasionally (covered).
If canning, cook in pressure cooker 15 minutes at 10 pounds pressure.
If not canning, cook additional 30 minutes.

title: weenie chowder
directions: Cut weenies and veggies into small pieces.
Saute in margarine.
Stir in flour.
Slowly add 1/2 cup milk, stirring constantly, to make a paste.
Add rest of the milk and stir. Remove from heat; add cheese.
Stir until melted.

title: patchwork casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat; drain.
Add peppers and onion; cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese; mix well.
Spoon half of meat and potato mixture into a 13 1/2 x 8 1/4-inch baking dish or 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with half of cheese.
Top with remaining meat and potato mixture.
Cover with aluminum foil or dish cover.
Bake 45 minutes.
Uncover dish. Top with remaining cheese.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serve with salad. Makes 12 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter together.
Melt butter in 8 x 8-inch casserole dish.
Pour in mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until it starts to brown on top.

title: deviled eggs with ham
directions: Tip:
Eggs may be filled ahead, covered and refrigerated up to 8 hours.
At serving time, arrange atop lettuce and sprinkle with reserved egg yolk and ham.

title: make-ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Cook or boil pared potatoes until tender; drain.
In a large bowl mash with a potato masher or beat with electric mixer on low speed. Add sour cream, cream cheese, 1 tablespoon margarine or butter, salt, pepper and thyme.
Gradually beat in enough of the milk to make smooth and fluffy.
Turn into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover with foil and chill up to 24 hours.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Pour 1/2 of batter into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 15 minutes.
Melt oleo, caramels and milk; stir.
Pour mixture over cake.
Sprinkle remaining nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour remaining batter over top.
Bake another 20 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: spicy potato soup
directions: In a Dutch oven or large kettle, brown ground beef.
Drain. Add potatoes, onion, and tomato sauce.
Stir in water, salt, pepper and hot pepper sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender and the soup has thickened.	Yield:	6-8 servings or 2 quarts.

title: american lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and garlic.
Add tomatoes and seasonings. Simmer for 20 minutes.
Cook lasagna noodles according to directions on package.
After draining, cover with cold water until used.

title: marinated turkey breast
directions: Combine all ingredients except bacon in a 1-gallon zip-seal bag; marinate 24 hours in the refrigerator. Remove meat from marinade; lay in a greased baking pan and cover each piece with a strip of bacon. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, then turn oven to broil and watch closely until browned.

title: baked ziti
directions: Saute
sausage,
beef,	mushrooms, onions and garlic in olive oil.
Drain excess liquid.	Add oregano, peppers, tomato sauce and tomatoes.
Let simmer for 30 minutes.
Mix pasta and 8 ounces of cheese in a large casserole dish.
Pour sauce over top of pasta, fully covering it.	Put remaining cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until bubbly.

title: sausage and egg breakfast casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a 9 x 9-inch baking dish. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Just as good reheated as when freshly baked.

title: fish chowder
directions: Cut bacon into 1/2-inch pieces.
Cook in large kettle until crispy brown.
Turn often.
Remove bits of bacon and reserve.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Cook raisins for 10 minutes or until water has cooked down. Cool butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks and raisins.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in slow oven (325°) for 40 minutes or until done.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix first 6 ingredients by hand.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Turn down oven to 300° and continue baking 20 to 25 minutes.

title: manicotti
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain off grease.
Add garlic salt, pepper, parsley and oregano.
Mix well.
In a bowl, crumble the bread. Add milk, egg and 8 ounces Mozzarella cheese.
Mix well. Add this to the ground beef mixture. Cook until cheese melts.

title: caramel and chocolate slice
directions: Base:
Combine flour, brown sugar, coconut and 9 tablespoons melted butter.
Mix well and press into greased 28 cm x 18 cm x 1 cm pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: texas trash
directions: In an 11 x 15-inch cookie sheet, combine Chex, pretzels, nuts, crackers and Fritos.
In a saucepan, melt margarine, then add Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder, onion salt, chili powder and, if desired, Tabasco sauce and dry onion.

title: quick and easy risotto
directions: Heat oil in saucepan. Add mushrooms and onions. Cook and stir on medium heat 5 minutes or until tender. Stir in rice, water and wine. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low. Cover. Simmer 20 minutes or until rice is tender. Stir in 1/2 cup of the cheese and half and half. Serve with remaining cheese. Makes 4 to 6 servings. Preparation time: 10 minutes. Cooking time: 25 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple together.
Add marshmallows, nuts and Cool Whip and blend.
Chill before serving.

title: fried corn
directions: Cut corn from cob and add milk, salt and pepper.
Put butter in heavy skillet.
When hot, add corn.
Cook until tender, stirring occasionally.
Just before ready to serve, add beaten eggs and blend in well.
Serve hot.

title: quick potato, meat meal
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together as meat loaf, but press it into 8-inch pie tins.
Bake in oven at 400° for about 15 minutes, or until done.
Fill meat crust with mashed potato filling.
Shave cheese and place on top.
Place back into oven.
Bake, until cheese has melted, in oven at 375° to 475°.
Serve hot.

title: marie's date cookies
directions: Cook dates, sugar and water until thick.
Stir often and blend in lemon juice and margarine.
Cool.

title: sauteed zucchini strips
directions: Cut zucchini into 1/4-inch thick strips, about 2 to 3-inches long.
In nonstick skillet, melt butter and saute zucchini, onion and garlic, stirring constantly.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper and oregano.
Simmer until tender.
Turn into greased casserole dish. Cover with cheese and bake at 350° until brown.

title: chili
directions: In large pan, empty pork and beans.
Add enough water, about 2 cans.
Bring to a boil while preparing hamburger meat.
In a skillet, brown meat, onion and garlic.
When brown, add tomato sauce and chili powder.
Cook for a minute, then add to beans. Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.

title: imitation crabmeat imperial
directions: Saute green pepper, celery and pimiento in melted butter in a large skillet until tender.
Stir in parsley, Old Bay seasoning, mustard, hot sauce and red pepper.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Cream together butter, brown sugar and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
In another bowl, mix together flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and soda.
Mix everything together and add chocolate chips, Hershey bar and nuts.

title: good quick hot rolls
directions: Mix yeast, sugar and warm water.
Let stand for 3 minutes. Add salt.
Mix rest of ingredients and add to yeast mixture.
Let set at least 30 minutes in warm place.
Punch down and make into rolls.
Let set 10 to 15 minutes.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer first 6 ingredients in a large salad bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and cheese.
Spread over other ingredients. Sprinkle with bacon bits.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a small bowl. Slowly whisk in oil. Store in refrigerator.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed, adding coconut flavoring and 2/3 cup coconut.
Bake as directed, using 9 x 13-inch pan.
Remove cake from oven.
Punch holes throughout and pour over the following mixture.
Mix water and milk to make 2 cups liquid.
Dissolve powdered sugar into this and add 1 teaspoon coconut flavor.
When cake is cool, frost with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle top with remaining coconut.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Whip sweet potatoes, then add sugar and cream.
Melt 3/4 stick margarine and marshmallows.
Add marshmallow mixture to cream mixture, then add eggs and vanilla.
Pour in greased 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Top with 3/4 stick melted margarine, 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup cereal or nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: bahamian salad
directions: Basic ingredient is cabbage or use whatever you have in your dehydrator, such as, onion, pepper, celery, carrot, radish, tomato, etc.
Add salt and pepper.
Secret is mayonnaise mixed with lime (fresh) juice.
Use your own taste buds!

title: scrumptious brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine in saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly.
Cool slightly.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat cheese until creamy; gradually add sugar.
Beat in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Blend well.
Spoon into a graham cracker crust.
Chill.

title: cobbler
directions: Melt margarine/butter in 2-quart baking dish.
Combine dry ingredients and stir into melted butter.
Add milk and stir again. Bring fruit and sugar to boil.
As soon as it boils, remove from heat and pour over batter.
Don't stir.
Bake at 400°
for about 30 minutes.

title: pleated potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes crosswise into 1/4-inch slices, taking care not to cut all the way through so that potato remains intact.
Place cut side up in a shallow pan coated with cooking spray.
Combine remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Brush potatoes with margarine mixture.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until tender and slices have fanned out.
Baste occasionally with pan drippings. Yield:
6 servings (90 calories per serving).

title: sloppy joes for 60
directions: Brown ground beef and onion (salted), then drain.
Add water, oats, chili powder and catsup or catsup and Manwich.
Cook slowly 1 hour.

title: cutout cookies
directions: Combine dry ingredients with butter.
Cut in with 2 knives or pastry blender.
Add egg and vanilla; mix with hands.
Dough will be very soft.
Knead a little flour into dough as you roll it out. Bake at 400° for 7 to 8 minutes, according to thickness of cookies and oven.

title: marshmallow popcorn balls
directions: Combine marshmallows and butter in a Dutch oven.
Cook over low heat until marshmallows melt, stirring mixture occasionally. Place popped corn, tossing to coat.
Coat hands with vegetable cooking spray.
Shape mixture into balls on wax paper to cool. Wrap individually in colored cellophane or plastic wrap.
Store in cool, dry place.
Yield: 16 balls.

title: rice and green chili casserole
directions: Mix and place in greased dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Top with Cheddar and return to oven until cheese melts.

title: dessert-a-la-ritz
directions: Crush Ritz crackers, reserving 1/2 cup crumbs.
Stir melted margarine into remaining crumbs and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill.

title: light caramel sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients except yogurt in a small saucepan. Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Boil 8 minutes without stirring.
Cool to room temperature.
Add yogurt; blend well.

title: small pecan butter cookies
directions: Mix well and form into balls.
Press down with a fork.
Bake for 7 minutes at 350°.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix and beat 4 minutes.
Bake in 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: microwaved baked potatoes
directions: With medium potato stick 3 or 4 times with fork.
Cook on High power for 3 minutes per potato.
Take out when finished and place potato on 2 layers of paper towels and cover with glass dish for 5 minutes.
Serve.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together margarine, peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Roll into bite-size balls and refrigerate or place in freezer until ready to dip in chocolate.

title: date loaf
directions: Boil sugar, milk and dates until it forms soft ball in water. Remove from fire and let cool to lukewarm.
Add vanilla and nuts and beat until firm enough to form 1 or 2-inch roll.
Pour in wet cloth; tie each end.
Hang up and let remain until cold.
Then slice.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Clean carrots with vegetable brush; slice the fresh carrots (not too large).
Steam fresh carrots or drain canned carrots. Slice green bell pepper and onion into rings.
Combine with cooked carrots.
Combine all other ingredients and pour over vegetables. Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
This keeps very well.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10-inch pie plate.
Cook and stir beef and onion until brown; drain.
Stir in salt and pepper. Spread beef in pie pan.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour over beef.
Bake until brown, about 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: poor man's crab cakes
directions: Grate zucchini.
Add all ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop in hot pan with very little Crisco by heaping tablespoons.
Cook on medium heat.
Turn cake one time.
Makes about 8.
Truly delicious!

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream together butter, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Sift flour and salt together; add to butter mixture with the nuts.
Chill dough 3 hours.

title: spicy turkey roast
directions: Put turkey breast in pan, skin side down.
Combine garlic, pepper, salt and rosemary in blender.
Add oil; chop all together. Spread 1/2 of mixture over turkey.
Bake on rack in roasting pan (300°) for 1 hour.
Put remaining mixture on turkey roast.
Finish baking at 300° until done.
Use juices from turkey to baste during cooking time.

title: caramel pie
directions: In heavy pan (better iron skillet), brown until dark the 1 cup sugar, stirring constantly.
At the same time, mix 1/2 cup sugar, flour, salt, egg yolks and milk in saucepan.
Place over medium heat, stirring constantly until somewhat thickened.
Pour into burnt sugar and cook over low heat until smooth.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
May add meringue.
Stirring both requires some coordination.

title: 5-flavor pound cake
directions: Mix sugar, butter and shortening until creamed.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add baking powder and flour.
Add all flavorings and milk.
Mix well.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: caramel cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and dry ingredients and knead well.
Form in long rolls and chill.
When real firm, slice and bake in 400° oven.

title: pineapple topping or cake filling
directions: In a heavy pan, combine all ingredients; bring to boil.
Stir 2 minutes or until clear.
Remove from heat.
Cool.
This is good on cheesecake or as a cake filling layer.

title: easy chicken stroganoff
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, in 1 tablespoon hot margarine, cook half the chicken until browned, stirring often. Remove; set aside.
Repeat with remaining chicken.
Reduce heat to medium.
In same skillet, in remaining 1 tablespoon hot margarine, cook mushrooms and onions until vegetables are tender and liquid is evaporated, stirring often.
Stir in soup and sour cream.
Heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Serve over noodles.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 4 servings.
Preparation time:
15 minutes; cooking time:
20 minutes.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening; add sugar gradually.
Beat until smooth.
Add egg yolks; beat well.
Combine flour and soda; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla, coconut and pecans; fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Pour into 3 greased and paper-lined 8-inch pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes; let cool.

title: chicken green bean casserole
directions: Remove chicken from bones and cut into bite size pieces. Spray a 7 x 10 x 2-inch pan with Pam and arrange drained green beans over bottom.
Place half of the boned chicken over green beans.
Top with whole crackers.
Cover the crackers with cheese slices; arrange remaining chicken over the cheese.
Combine soup, broth, onion flakes and 1/4 cup grated cheese.
Pour over chicken. Sprinkle casserole with cracker crumbs and mushrooms.
Drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
This can be doubled for a larger casserole.

title: herbed potatoes
directions: Coat large baking dish with cooking spray.
Layer half each of potatoes, onion and tomatoes in dish; sprinkle with half of salt, thyme and rosemary.
Repeat layers and drizzle with the olive oil. Cover and bake at 425° for 35 to 40 minutes or tender.
Sprinkle with parsley.
(If no fresh parsley, sprinkle with 1 tablespoon dry crushed before baking.)

title: hamburger barbecue
directions: In a large skillet, cook together beef, peppers and onions, stirring with a fork to break up meat, until meat is browned and vegetables are tender.
Drain off excess drippings.
In a small bowl, mix together remaining ingredients, except buns.
Add to beef mixture in pan.
Mix well; cook over low heat for 50 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Spoon on buns.
Serve immediately.

title: pizza omelet
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter or margarine in 8-inch skillet.
Beat eggs with milk and pour into hot skillet.
Tilt pan to spread eggs over bottom.
When eggs are almost dry, spread sauce, oregano and cheese over one-half of eggs.
Add optional toppings, if desired and carefully fold unfilled half over fillings.
Cover and warm over low heat until cheese is melted.

title: ham-stuffed rolls(microwave)
directions: Combine ham with eggs, onion, pepper, mustard, relish and mayonnaise.
Cut off tops of rolls; scoop out.
Fill with ham mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Place in 7 1/2 x 12-inch baking dish.
Cook on Medium for 3 minutes.
Turn dish.
Cook 2 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 sandwiches.

title: pennsylvania dutch peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring to a boil, lower heat and boil for 3 minutes. Remove from heat, add peanut butter, mix and blend until it starts to thicken. Pour into 8 inch greased pan. Let cool and cut.

title: spinach balls
directions: Drain spinach thoroughly.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Form into balls.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake for 25 minutes.

title: pork and macaroni casserole(yields 100 servings)
directions: Place ground pork in a 21 x 13 x 2 1/2-inch pan.
Cook meat in a 375° oven for 45 minutes.
Mix well to break into small pieces. Pour off drippings and save.
Season with salt and paprika.
Break tomatoes and add instant minced onion.
Let stand 20 minutes. Cook macaroni in salted water and oil; do not overcook.
Drain. In saucepot or kettle, combine soup, garlic salt, pepper, basil and savory.
Mix well and heat.
Add tomato and onion mixture.
In 2 pans (21 x 13 x 2 1/2-inch), place half the pork and half the macaroni, then half of the celery and tomato mixture.
Cover and bake in a 375° oven for 35 to 45 minutes or until hot.
Uncover and sprinkle with 8 ounces grated cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Blend soup and milk in a 6 cup casserole.
Mix in tuna, noodles, beans and onions; top with buttered bread crumbs (toast, butter and crumble).
Bake in a hot 400° oven for 25 minutes or until bubbly hot.

title: pistachio pudding
directions: Drain pineapple, but save some juice.
Mix all ingredients with your hands adding some of the pineapple juice.
Put in bowl or casserole dish and refrigerate.

title: salsa dip
directions: Brown sausage over medium heat.
Drain the grease off the sausage.
In a medium size casserole dish, mix the salsa and the sausage together.
Then cut 1/2-inch square cubes of cheese and add them to the salsa.
Place dish in microwave and heat for about 3 minutes.
Stir salsa thoroughly.
Complete this cycle until cheese is thoroughly melted.

title: lazy pierogis
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
You may need a little more flour.
Roll dough 2 inches in diameter.
Cut into 1/2-inch pieces. Cook in boiling water about 5 minutes (when pieces come to the top).
Put into colander to drain.
Butter a serving dish and place these pieces on it.
Pour some sauteed onions over the layers.

title: hot mulled punch
directions: Put the juices in a 22-cup coffeemaker.
Put the sugar and spices in the basket of the coffeemaker.
Perk and serve.
Great for the holidays.
Serves 20.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Layer in 9 x 12-inch pan as follows:
ground beef (raw, place in thin layer), Cheddar cheese soup, corn and Tater Tots.
Bake in 400° oven for 55 minutes.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top and return to oven until cheese melts.
Serve immediately.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Keeps the mess in your oven, not all over your kitchen.
Coat chicken pieces with flour in a plastic bag.
Make sure they are coated well. Heat butter and Crisco in a 13 x 9-inch pan in 425° oven until melted.
Place chicken in pan.
Bake 30 minutes.
Turn. Bake 30 more minutes.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Sprinkle the cucumber with salt and let stand 25 minutes. Sprinkle the onion rings with the paprika.
Place all the ingredients in a glass jar and refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Leave crescent rolls in their rectangular shapes.
You should have 4 rectangles.
Spread sausage onto the rolls.
Roll up into rolls.
Slice into thin slices and bake in hot oven until sausage is cooked and rolls are brown.
These are delicious served warm.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Dump cake mix in bowl and reserve 1 cup to the bowl.
Add melted margarine and beaten egg.
Stir and spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
(Batter will be stiff).
Set aside.
Make Filling.

title: red-hot cinnamon cider
directions: In medium saucepan, combine apple cider and candies.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 4 minutes or until candies dissolve.
Serve hot or cold.
May be frozen.

title: graham cracker crunch
directions: Cook butter and sugar over low fire.
Cook over low fire until starts to brown around edges of butter and sugar.
Take off fire and add your pecans and vanilla and drop onto graham crackers.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Lightly grease and flour pan (large tube pan).
Set oven at 350°.
Mix together first 8 items.
Mix apples, cinnamon and sugar.
Put thin layer of batter, then apples.
Alternate and end with a layer of apples.
Bake 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Cool. Remove from pan and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: strawberry ice cream(sorbet)
directions: Mash the fruit in a food processor.
Add the sugar and lemon juice and mix until the sugar is dissolved.
Mix with the whipped cream.
Pour in a freezerproof container, preferably a flat one, so it will freeze faster.
Set freezer at maximum freezing capacity and put the container in the freezer.
After an hour, remove the container from the freezer and stir its contents well.
Use mixer or food processor if you like.
Reduce freezer setting to normal operating temperature/freezing capacity.
Put the container back in the freezer.
Preferably, repeat this procedure after another hour again.
Count on a total freezing time of at least 3 hours.
Serves 4 persons.

title: never-fail divinity
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, 3/4 cup water and salt in a 2-quart glass casserole.
Microwave on High for 19 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes or to 260° on a candy thermometer.
Heat egg whites until very stiff.
Pour hot syrup gradually over egg whites, beating at high speed for about 12 minutes or until thick and candy begins to lose gloss.
Fold in vanilla and pecans.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: kensington club marinade
directions: Meats can be marinated in this sauce up to 8 days.
Can also be used as a basting sauce.
Terrific for chicken, pork, beef and fish.
With fish, only marinate overnight or a few hours.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour pan (9 x 13 x 2-inch).
Spread the pecans in pan.
Sprinkle the coconut in the pan.
Mix cake mix as directed; pour over coconut.
Melt margarine and cream cheese.
Add powdered sugar; pour over cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pound cake(norsk sandkake)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and flour.
Mix well.
Place in buttered and floured bread pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and rest of ingredients together.
Mix well; chill and shape into ball before serving.

title: date nut pudding
directions: Mix everything together.
Put in well-greased baking dish. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: lemon squares
directions: Blend and pat flat in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: family carrot cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients. Make a well in center of dry ingredients. Add eggs, oil and vanilla. Stir in pineapple, carrots and nuts. Turn into tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or bake in 3 round pans for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown and starting to separate from pan.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Blend butter and sugar well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Add buttermilk alternately with sifted dry ingredients.
Stir only enough to blend.
Add flavoring.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour in tube pan at 300°.

title: bourbon slush
directions: Steep the tea bags in 1 cup boiling water for 2 to 3 minutes. Remove tea bags.
Stir in sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix until sugar is dissolved.
Pour into a freezer container and freeze until firm.
Spoon slush into glasses.
Add Fresca, 50-50, Squirt, ginger ale or 7-Up.

title: health bread
directions: Combine raisins and 1 cup water in a saucepan. Bring to a boil and boil 5 minutes. Combine remaining ingredients in large bowl. Add raisins and water. Mix well. Grease 9 x 5 loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and eggs.
Add melted margarine, Karo, salt and vanilla.
Mix well. Add pecans last.
Bake pie shell in oven until lightly browned at 325° for about 5 to 8 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Pour pecan mixture in pie shell.
Bake at 325° to 350° until firm.

title: gazpacho soup
directions: Into blender, combine cukes and tomato juice.
Place in a non-metal container.
Blend all other vegetables except only 1/2 of onion.
Add juice of 2 lemons and pimientos, salsa, spices and sliced tomato.
Refrigerate and serve after a couple of hours or days.

title: marzetti
directions: Brown beef with onion.
Add the remaining ingredients, being generous with the garlic powder.
Simmer all until noodles are done.
Stir to keep from sticking.
Serves 4 generously.

title: oatmeal scotchies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl combine flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon, set aside.
In large bowl combine butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in oats and morsels.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes for chewier cookies or 9 to 10 minutes for crisper cookies.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: always perfect pie crust
directions: Mix first three ingredients until grainy.
Mix remaining with rest of mixture.
Roll crust.
Makes 3 pie crusts.
Bake at 425°.

title: barbecue sauerkraut
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet with onion and salt.
Drain off excess fat.
Put in a 2-quart casserole.
Add sauerkraut, brown sugar and tomato juice.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken brunswick stew
directions: Mix all ingredients, except fowl and spices.
Cook until beans are almost done.
Add the chicken or turkey and spices, and simmer about 30 minutes.

title: devil food cookies
directions: Mix above ingredients together and roll in small balls.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.
Remove from oven and let cool.
Fill with Betty Crocker can white (vanilla) icing. Makes about 30 double cookies.

title: grilled turkey
directions: Inject legs, thighs, breast and all other meaty parts of turkey with Cajun injector.
Store turkey, covered, in refrigerator overnight.
Place turkey in 4-inch deep foil pan (disposable).
Cover with foil.
Fill pan with water (at least 2-inches deep).
Place on very hot grill (high on gas grill) for 2 hours.
Turkey will be brown and very tender.
Check occasionally during cooking to add more water, if necessary.

title: spaghetti - italian sauce
directions: In large skillet, cook sausage until brown in olive oil. Remove sausage and wilt onions in oil.
Remove or drain oil from skillet.
Add rest of ingredients and cook about 5 minutes.
Add sausage and simmer, stirring often, for about 30 minutes.

title: sausage-onion snacks
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Cook and stir sausage and onion over medium heat until sausage is brown; drain.
Mix baking mix, milk and 1 egg.
Spread in pan.
Sprinkle with caraway seed.
Top with sausage mixture.
Mix sour cream, salt and remaining egg; pour evenly over sausage.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, until set, 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut in rectangles (approximately 2 x 1 1/2-inch).
Makes 32 appetizers.

title: chocolate layer dessert
directions: To Assemble in Bowl or
Punch Bowl:
Put 1/3 of the crumbled chocolate cake and top with 1/3 of the pudding, then sprinkle with 1/3 of the candy. Top with 1/3 Cool Whip. Repeat until ingredients are used.
Garnish with crushed candy or nuts.
Refrigerate. Great dish to make ahead.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine	and
eggs.
Beat
in
extracts, fruit and pecans.
Bake in
greased tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours. Cool before removing from pan.
Can be baked in 2 loaf pans.

title: maryann sawyer's wassail
directions: Put all but spices in large kettle.
Tie cloves and allspice in cheesecloth (add cinnamon sticks if you are not going to use individual cinnamon sticks in cups).
Add nutmeg and spice packet to liquid.
Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.
Remove bag; serve with individual cinnamon sticks, if desired.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Let the cream cheese soften.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: marshmallow krispie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan. Prepare brownies following package directions for original recipe. Remove from oven.
Sprinkle marshmallows over hot brownies.
Return to oven; bake 3 minutes longer.
Combine chocolate chips, peanut butter and butter in medium saucepan.
Cook on low heat, stirring constantly, until chips are melted.
Add Rice Krispies and mix well.
Spread over marshmallow layer.
Refrigerate until chilled. Cut into bars.
Makes 24.

title: dutch cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour and oleo like pie dough.
Save 1/2 cup for use as topping.
Add egg, milk with soda and vanilla.
Mix well all in 1 bowl.
Pour in well greased and floured cake pan (8-inch square pan).
Sprinkle with topping and cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
